<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/kha_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/kha_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> VA Beach VA Chase the Can 12/16/01<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.83)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=3604'>Mark "Rogue Nine" Balderston</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=3604&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> December 29, 2001</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Pre-tourney stuff: Yay Chase the Can . . . free packs !  My brother and I raid the closet for cans then go to the tournament.  I&#39;m playing a Gandalf/Sauron deck.<br>
<br>
Game 1: Brian Kallenbach&#39;s Gandalf/Moria.<br>
<br>
He starts the game with a foil Frodo, Old Bilbo&#39;s Heir AND a foil Isildur&#39;s Bane.  OOh, my precious . . . he outbids e but then . . .makes me go first.  So I put out Prnacing Pony and use it to pull Aragorn (surprise!) then I think I put out Boromir with the Blade of Gondor, I make it to site three fairly easily, killing a few annoying Moria Orcs on the way. He gets out the Underdeeps of Moria (uh-oh).  On his turn he goets out Aragorn (surprise again!) and Glamdring.  I put some Orcs out and I don&#39;t think he even really kills anyone, so he stops.  I get out Glamdring and use it to looka t his hand.  He has a couple of orcs and one of the cheap Uruk-hai.  Hmmm.  I&#39;m not drawing either Aragorn&#39;s Bow or rare Legolas, so I could have a problem if he comes down with lots of orcs.  I make it to site 5 fairly safelyh except for a Saruman&#39;s Snows which prevents me from playing any of the Servant of the Secret Fires I have in my hand.  It is hnighly unusual for my deck not to have drawn any Legolas or Aragorn&#39;s Bow by this point.  Brian sticks to his one site a turn for his fellowship while accumulating orcs in his hand.  His guys are taking hits from my orcs but since he is only moving one site a turn I can&#39;t really do much with my shadow side.  I stop at site sic to heal up a bit and he goes on to site four.  I get Albert Dreary and Sting and look at his hand where I see a mass or orcs that he&#39;s been piling up in his hand.  Crap.  No Aragorn&#39;s Bow, no Legolas.  Double crap.  I move on and he puts out his mass of guys using the Goblin Sneaks and the Underdeeps of Moria to put out around nine orcs.  Five of them get stacked on Frodo (who has Sting).  I make a joke about Power According to his Stature, but I don&#39;t really have it.   I play three Servant of the Secret Fires out of my hand and I get him down to around 13 strength.  One less orc and I would&#39; have still been alive.  But I&#39;m dead.  <br>
<br>
FL +1<br>
<br>
GAME ANALYSIS:  Luck Sucks . . . in playtesting I had almost always ha d Aragorn&#39;s Bow or Legolas by site 3.  Bleh.  Albert Dreary is awesome . . . a turn earlier and I would&#39;ve stopped that nasty Underdeeps thing.<br>
<br>
Game 2:  Brian Richards Legolas/Gimli deck.<br>
Brian has a rather, ahhh . . . unique deck . . . he starts with Legolas and Gimli and gets out Boromir and Aragorn later.  For some reason I just cannot remember the shadow cards he played this gmae.  I think it was Uruk-Hai.  Anyway I get out lots of companioons with weapons this game and slaughtered whatever minions he put out with aied archery ruthlessly, . . . after site three that is.  Before site three, I just took a crapload of wounds that I healed at the sanctuary.  Around site six or seven I play A Ranger&#39;s Versatility on two big bad Uruk-Hai, and since he has no other minions, they go down to the archery total without me even having to exert.  Nifty.  Anything that survives the archery phase from there dies to either Aragorn or Gandalf.  This is what my deck is designed to do . . . . sometimes it just doesn&#39;t happen.  So I get to site nine and he only has one minion in hand who dies to archery.  Ok, here&#39;s what happened for the shadow half.  He gets set up with Aragorn and GBoromir stuff I know that he&#39;s running a bunch of dwarf events (from scanning his hand with Glamdring) so Aragorn and Gimli both get Desperate Defense of the Ring and the burdens start stacking up.   Aragorn goes down relatively early to an Enduring Evil.  Gimli gets another Desperate Defense of the Ring and he&#39;s left witha bunch of dwarf car in hand that he can&#39;t use without adding burdens.  Boromir goes down to an Enduring Evil around site five.  At the next site I play an Enduring Evil on Gimli (after he adds a burden AND discards three cards), he plays something to save Gimli and I play another Enduring evili to kill him. mwahaha.  I move to site eight and stop just because it is smart for me to stop at eight when he is only at six.  He moves on to seven and just BARELY survives by exhausting Legolas to kill someone.  I move on to nine and win. <br>
<br>
GAME ANALYSIS: This is a good testament to the power of Enduring Evil . ..  when played at the right time.  What an awesome card.<br>
<br>
Game 3: Parker Williams Dwarves/Sauron (wounding)<br>
<br>
Parker starts with Gimli and the other dwarf Farin.  He outbids me (doh!) and goes first, starting (surprise) the Prancing Pony.  So he gets out Aragorn and gets Dwarf Axes on Gimli and Farin first turn.  Crap.  So whenever I pu t down orcs he plays two or three events and I lose cards off the top of my draw deck.  So he makes it to site after beating the crap out of my orcs.  I ge tdown Thin and Stretched, but I forgot to enforce it most of the time.  On my turn I go and get to stie theree pretty easily.  He was mainly running Orc War Bands and the like, Under the Watching Eye, etc.  Around five or six I use Sleep, Caradhras to get rid of those.  On his turn he gets down Greatest Kingdom of My People which is absolutely horrible for my deck because every time I play an orc, I watch another orc go off the top of my draw deck.  Aagh.  We both use Sting/Glamdring to keep thw twilight pool llow.  We&#39;re both moving two sites a turn while completely destroying each other&#39;s shadow side.  He stops at six and then stop at six to heal up.  This was a GAME-LOSING MISTAKE, because now I am hopelessly behind with NO chance of passing him.  If I had gone on to seven I could have made it to nine then next turn.  BUT . . . I didn&#39;t.  Anyway he gets to eight relatively safely since almost all my minions have been discarded now, and then I get to eight.  He goes to my ninth site which is SUmmit of Amon Hen so I get to draw the remainder of my draw deck, but there are absolutely no minions left since the shuffle placed them all near the top where they were hopelessly discarded by GKOMP.  I might have won from corruption if I had not forgotten about Thin and Stretched and been able to play just a couple more minions because then he would have been forced to add burdens from Desperate Defense of the Ring.  Oh well.  Oh yeah  . . . I forgot around site six or seven I killed Gimli with the one Enduring Evil I drew when I had minions in my hand.<br>
<br>
GAME ANALYSIS: many lessons learned here . . .<br>
1.  Going first is HUGE.<br>
2.  Don&#39;t stop at six unless you ABSOLUTELY have to when you&#39;re behind.<br>
3.  Don&#39;t forget about Thin and Stretched.<br>
4.  Greatest Kingdom of My People is Nasstyyy.<br>
<br>
Game 4: ?&#39;s Uruk-Hai/Nazgul/Hobbits<br>
<br>
Hmmm . . . I get to go first and I have the craziest hand I have ever seen.  First I pull Aragorn.  Then I put down Glamdring and scan his hand.  No Moria, good.  Having thus ensured my safety, I proceed to put down Albert Dreary, Boromir, Arwen, AND Legolas.  I move on and he has 2 twilight pool.  HOly cow.  He puts down some Uruk-Hai and Nzgul at sitew two and three, but they are inconsequential because noone dies and I get to site three safely.  The rest of this game was pretty boring compared to the others.  He has some stealthy hobbits, but I exert to wound with all the orcs in the first skirmish so that I&#39;m still causing damage.  He ends up having to move one site at a time most of the time.  I&#39;m beating up Uruk-Hai left and right.  To make a long, boring story short, I get to site eight where Gandalf dies then at site nine I let everyone except Frodo die, so I win.<br>
<br>
After-tournament fun game: Brian Casimiro<br>
<br>
This is included for all of you who doubt that Sauron can win in the early-game.  Ok so I revamp my deck afterwards into a kind of Aragorn/Boromir??Gandalf thing.  Anyway I bid five and go first then use Green Dragon INn to pull Sam and get rid of three burdens.  I putdown Boroir and make it to site three against some Moria Orcs fairly safely.  He goes and pulls Sam (started w/Aragorn, KIE) and moves on giving me a total of seven twilight pool.  Not exactly enough for a beatdown, you&#39;d think?  Anyway I put out an orc assassin (2 +2 roaming) an orc soldier (2+ 1 roaming), play two forces of mordor (+2 twilight, +2 twilight), play an orc inquisitor, and then put thin and stretched on Frodo. Frodo gets assigned to the orc assassin, and I play Enduring Evil which puts Frodo down to a strength three compared to the Orc Assassin&#39;s six strength and I win the game at site two.  Nifty. <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3220&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
